      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Here's a roundup of the latest AI news today:\n\n---\n\n### 🔥 Key Headlines\n\n1. **Musk vs. Altman Trial Underway**\n   "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The civil trial between the tech billionaires kicked off Monday and could help define the future of artificial intelligence."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": " "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Musk was at times boastful and snarky, using the witness stand to attack Sam Altman. He claimed Altman betrayed the original principles of OpenAI to remain a nonprofit and that the company benefited from his money and connections."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n2. **AI Security Concerns — \"Mythos\" Warnings**\n   "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "An AI company's own experts warned Mythos could hack the systems beneath most modern computing. Banks and government agencies are racing to gauge the threat."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n3. **Google Cloud Revenue Surges**\n   "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The AI infrastructure arms race hits full throttle as Alphabet breaks away with a 63% surge in Google Cloud revenue to US$20bn for Q1 2026."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n4. **AI \"World Models\" Gaining Momentum**\n   "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Some researchers, including AI pioneer Yann LeCun, who founded Advanced Machine Intelligence (AMI) Labs in Paris, have turned their attention to developing systems known as 'world models' that are trained on real-world data and can embody virtual, interactive and 3D environments."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": " "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "AMI Labs has raised more than US$1 billion, a record initial infusion of money for a European company. Technology giants such as Google and Nvidia are also developing world models."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n5. **AI in Defense & Military**\n   "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Google joins OpenAI in allowing the Pentagon to use its AI systems, as rival Anthropic remains embroiled in a court battle after seeking stronger safeguards."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": " "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The high-stakes conflict between the Defense Department and a $380 billion tech powerhouse goes to the heart of just how far AI can go in warfare."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n6. **DeSantis Pushes AI Legislation**\n   "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The governor is emerging as a voice of AI skepticism in the Republican Party, but state lawmakers declined to take up DeSantis' push for legislation."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n7. **Data Center Moratorium Bill**\n   "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "A bill had passed both chambers of the state Legislature and would have imposed the country's first statewide moratorium on new data center construction."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n8. **AI Agents on the Rise**\n   "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Many companies are increasingly looking to agents as a way to boost employee productivity and automate rote chores."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n---\n\n### 🔬 Research & Innovation (MIT)\n\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "A new dataset of 30,000-plus competition math problems from 47 countries gives AI researchers a harder test — and students worldwide a better training ground."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "A new training method improves the reliability of AI confidence estimates without sacrificing performance, addressing a root cause of hallucination in reasoning models."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Building on a long-standing MIT–IBM collaboration, a new lab will chart the convergence of AI, algorithms, and quantum computing."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n---\n\n### 🏢 Industry Moves\n\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Tim Cook is stepping down as CEO after serving Apple for 15 years, leaving John Ternus as his successor."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Rogo, started by young bankers around a kitchen table in 2021, just won a multibillion-dollar valuation."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Amazon's new Connect Talent — now available in preview — uses AI \"teammates\" to conduct 24/7 interviews and score candidates."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\nThe AI landscape continues to evolve rapidly with major legal battles, record-breaking investments, and significant advances in research and applications."
      }
